should be concentrated in a separate ﬁle that can be placed into .gitignore, but sometimes as a short-term
solution it can be helpful to have something local in a checked-in ﬁle.
You can make Git "unsee" those lines using clean ﬁlter. They won't even show up in diﬀs.
Suppose here is snippet from ﬁle file1.c:
struct settings s;
s.host "localhost";
s.port 5653;
s.auth 1;
s.port 15653; NOCOMMIT
s.debug 1; NOCOMMIT
s.auth 0; NOCOMMIT
You don't want to publish NOCOMMIT lines anywhere.
